using UnityEngine;

public class ChallengeError : MonoBehaviour
{
    void OnCollisionEnter2D(Collision2D collision)
    {
        // Forgot to check if the enemy is alive before destroying
        Destroy(collision.gameObject);  // Destroys everything!
    }
}

phase2.explanation:
Without checking the tag, the collision destroys any object it touches — including the player.

**The fix:**
```csharp
void OnCollisionEnter2D(Collision2D collision)
{
    if (collision.gameObject.CompareTag("Enemy"))
    {
        Destroy(collision.gameObject);
    }
}
```

**Sharp-chan says:**
"Always check tags before destroying objects. Otherwise, you'll destroy things you didn't mean to."
